added.title: Movie Night
added.description: It's Movie Night and the Titans have a hard time deciding who gets to choose which movie they watch.

added.title: Labor Day
added.description: It's Labor Day and Robin teaches the other Titans about the importance of labor.

added.title: Classic Titans
added.description: To prove his point about classic superhero cartoons, Control Freak sends the Titans to a former version of Teen Titans Go!

added.title: Throne of Bones
added.description: When the other Titans start listening to heavy metal music, Robin warns them of the dangers.

added.title: Dignity of Teeth
added.description: When Beast Boy gets a stack of cash from the Tooth Fairy, against Raven's advice the other Titans start knocking out their own teeth to get some of that sweet Tooth Fairy money.

added.title: Spice Game
added.description: Tired of Robin's bland cooking, the other Titans try their hand at spicing up their food.

added.title: The Fourth Wall
added.description: Control Freak informs the Titans that they are on a TV show he created and demands they earn him an award.

added.title: Garage Sale
added.description: Robin makes the other Titans sell their treasured mementos from past episodes.

added.title: Booty Scooty
added.description: In order to save Titans Tower from some wealthy land developers, the Titans search for pirate treasure.

added.title: Mr. Butt
added.description: After Starfire is set up by Blackfire and sent to prison, the Titans work to make Blackfire a better sister while Starfire plots her revenge.

added.title: Video Game References
added.description: The Titans immerse themselves in different video game worlds.

added.title: Laundry Day
added.description: When the gang bickers over whose turn it is to do chores, things quickly get out of control until their dirty uniforms grow a mind of their own and attack!

added.title: Birds
added.description: Robin tries to destroy some pesky mocking birds but they come back bigger, stronger, and ready to mock.

added.title: Charlie Ball
added.description: After Panda gets injured on the basketball court, the Bears invite Charlie to be on their basketball team. But when Charlie gets too good, he starts to ruin all the fun of the game.

added.title: Rooms
added.description: The Bears switch bedrooms for the night and get a glimpse of the living space of one of their brothers. But the deeper they go, hidden secrets are revealed.

added.title: Losing Ice
added.description: Feeling unappreciated, Ice Bear leaves his brothers to be the chef of a restaurant. Desperate to fill the void, Grizz and Panda look for Ice Bear's replacement.

added.title: The Island
added.description: While trying to sail to Japan, the Baby Bears get stranded on an island. Luckily, they meet Dave and Karla, who help with survival on the island while looking for an escape.

added.title: Brother Up
added.description: After Panda stumbles and accidentally scares a pack of wolves away in the process, the hierarchy of the Bears is disrupted. Suddenly, Panda has become the alpha bear, and he and Grizz have to deal with the consequences of an emotional Panda being the leader of the three Bears.

added.title: Occupy Bears
added.description: When the city plans to destroy the Bears' cave in order to make way for a new cell phone tower, Grizz and Panda must find evidence from their past that proves they have rights to their land. And in case that fails, Ice Bear protests and tries to sabotage the construction crew.

added.title: Panda's Sneeze
added.description: Panda bears have a very adorable (and violent!) sneeze, and our Panda is no exception. When a Vine video of his very cute sneeze goes viral, Panda becomes a cute sensation, which causes Nom Nom to try to fend off of this new challenger to his throne.

added.title: Emergency
added.description: When Grizz comes home with a live crab, he thinks it can become a pet for the brothers to share. However, after the crab pinches Ice Bear's ear and won't let go, Panda and Grizz have to get their injured brother to the hospital, and fast!

added.title: Cupcake Job
added.description: When the Bears' beloved laptop breaks, they finally have the need to do something they've never done before: get jobs. Working at a trendy cupcake shop, the Bears find  that the working world is much tougher than they realized.

added.title: Hibernation
added.description: The bears, being an urban bunch, hadn't ever heard of the idea of hibernation until Chloe tells them about it. Grizz, loving the idea of eating a ton and then just sleeping to his heart's content, goes for it with reckless abandon.  But Grizz is so excited for hibernating... that he can't fall asleep.

added.title: Saturday School
added.description: After creating an unapproved mural on a wall at Aberdale Elementary, Clarence, Jeff and Sumo are forced to come to school on a Saturday to clean up as punishment.

added.title: Field Trippin'
added.description: After a pit stop bathroom break during a school field trip, Clarence returns to the parking lot and accidentally gets on the wrong school bus - which takes him to a different school!

added.title: Skater Sumo
added.description: As Sumo and Clarence are playing outside, Chelsea and Rita skate by on their new skateboards. Enthralled, Sumo decides to build his own and join their skating team, while Clarence seems to have other ideas.

added.title: Plant Daddies
added.description: When Ms. Baker pairs up the kids to act as parents for a sprout, Sumo and Clarence learn all about good parenting. Jeff buys toys instead of fertilizer and Chelsea and Kimby get to know each other.

added.title: Hoofin' It
added.description: It's time for the annual Aberdale Greased Pig Chase and everyone's excited except Clarence. He feels so bad for poor little pig Butterscotch that he takes her place in the pig chase, running from townsfolk eager to take home the prized barrel full of hot dogs!

added.title: Benson's Pig
added.description: Mordecai and Rigby have to take Benson's new pet pig back to his apartment.

added.title: California King
added.description: Rigby wins a king-size bed and throws his trampoline bed in the garbage. But when he realizes that he can't sleep without his trampoline, he has to go through an elaborate junkyard to find it.

added.title: Benson's Suit
added.description: Benson wants to feel better about himself.

added.title: Benson's Car
added.description: Mordecai and Rigby have to fix Benson's car before he finds out they broke its window.

added.title: A Skips in Time
added.description: Mordecai and Rigby have to help Skips return Teenage Skips to the 1700s.

added.title: Bad Portrait
added.description: Mordecai and Rigby have to re-paint Benson's portrait for a party.

added.title: Catching the Wave
added.description: Pops wants to catch a wave.

added.title: Bachelor Party! Zingo!
added.description: Skips must plan the perfect bachelor party for his cousin, Quips.

added.title: Caveman
added.description: Mordecai and Rigby want to civilize a caveman so that Benson will let him stay at the park.

added.title: A Bunch of Full Grown Geese
added.description: Mordecai and Rigby have to get rid of some geese that are causing problems at the park.

added.title: Bet to Be Blonde
added.description: Rigby wins a bet with Mordecai and makes him get a blonde perm.

added.title: Bad Kiss
added.description: Mordecai finally makes his move and tries to kiss Margaret.

added.title: Appreciation Day
added.description: By trying to change Benson's opinion of them, Mordecai and Rigby accidentally create lots of work for themselves.

added.title: A Bunch of Baby Ducks
added.description: Mordecai and Rigby come across a family of ducks living in a fountain at the park and take quite a shine to them.

removed.description: The Titans are having a terrible time on their camping trip so Robin suggests that they each tell a scary campfire story.

removed.title: Costume Contest

removed.title: Ones and Zeros

removed.title: Oregon Trail
